To facilitate the resumption of this project in a new conversation, here is a summary of what has been implemented in the app/modules/core/config.py file:

Objective
Centralize and protect environment variables, ensuring that sensitive credentials (such as the Neon.tech connection string) are not exposed in the code.

Technical Implementation
Use of the python-dotenv library to load variables from a .env file (local development) or from the operating system (production on GCE).

Creation of the Config class that encapsulates access to DATABASE_URL_Neon and SECRET_KEY.

Implementation of a critical check (if not DATABASE_URL) that halts execution with a ValueError if the connection variable is not configured, preventing silent failures in the application.

Execution Configuration
In environments such as PyCharm, the DATABASE_URL_Neon variable must be injected through Run Configurations (Environment variables field), ensuring that the config.py file is successfully loaded when imported by the other modules of the application.

